question: Jake has 7 fewer peaches than Steven and 9 more peaches than Jill. Steven has 16 peaches. How many peaches does Jake have?
response:
Jake has 7 fewer peaches than Steven, so Jake has 16 - 7 = <<16-7=9>>9 peaches.
Jake has 9 more peaches than Jill, so Jake has 9 + 7 = <<9+7=16>>16 peaches.
The answer is 16.
